## Shared Systemic Defects

### CRITICAL: `parent` Field in Frontmatter
**All 7 skills** include `parent: use-hivemind` in YAML frontmatter.

Per the HiveMind SKILL.md authoring standard, frontmatter MUST contain ONLY:
- `name`
- `description`

The `parent` field is PROHIBITED. This is a CRITICAL defect in all 7 files.

| File | Line |
|------|------|
| hivemind-synthesis/SKILL.md | 4 |
| hivemind-system-debug/SKILL.md | 4 |
| use-hivemind-ideating/SKILL.md | 4 |
| use-hivemind-planning/SKILL.md | 3 |
| use-hivemind-research/SKILL.md | 4 |
| use-hivemind-skill-authoring/SKILL.md | 4 |
| use-hivemind-tdd/SKILL.md | 3 |

### HIGH: `<!-- LOAD-POSITION -->` HTML Comments in Body
**All 7 skills** contain HTML comment blocks with meta directives in the body.

Example (from hivemind-synthesis, lines 7-11):
```html
<!-- LOAD-POSITION
slot: depth
role: depth
prerequisites: use-hivemind-delegation, use-hivemind-research
-->
```

This pattern appears in all 7 files. These are stray meta comments that should not exist in SKILL.md body content.

### MEDIUM: Second-Person Writing Style
**All 7 skills** are written in second-person voice ("you", "your").

Example patterns:
- "You need this skill when..." 
- "Before you decompose..."
- "You think the spec is clear enough..."
- "If you're building a skill..."

Per the authoring standard, SKILL.md should use imperative/infinitive form (verb-first) or third-person.

Count across all 7 files: 175+ second-person instances.

